{
    "word": "Swindler",
    "definitions": [
        "One who swindles, or defrauds grossly; one who makes a practice of defrauding others by imposition or deliberate artifice; a cheat."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "Fraud and injustice soon follow, and the dignity of the British merchant is sunk in the scandalous appellation of a swindler.",
        "Perhaps you 'll think I act the same As a sly sharper plays his game."
    ],
    "etymology": "[G. schwindler, fr. schwindlen to be dizzy, to act thoughtlessly, to cheat, fr. schwindel dizziness, fr. schwinden to vanish, to disappear, to dwindle. See Swim to be dizzy.]"
}